  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Where can I rent a big apartment in Seattle and not pay too much money?",
  "response": "Finding a spacious yet affordable apartment in Seattle can be challenging, but there are strategies you can use to find a good deal:\n\n1. **Neighborhood Choice:** Look for neighborhoods that tend to have lower rental prices. Areas like Northgate, Beacon Hill, White Center, and Rainier Valley often have more affordable housing options compared to bustling neighborhoods like Capitol Hill or Downtown Seattle.\n\n2. **Expand your Search Radius:** Consider living just outside the city limits in nearby suburbs like Shoreline, Burien, or Renton, where rents may be lower while still offering reasonable commuting options into Seattle.\n\n3. **Look for Older Buildings:** Apartments in older, less modernized buildings may have lower rents compared to newer luxury developments. These can often be better deals in terms of space.\n\n4. **Shared Accommodations:** Consider renting a larger apartment and finding roommates to share the cost. This can significantly reduce your rent per person while still providing ample space.\n\n5. **Time Your Search:** Rental prices can fluctuate throughout the year. It may be beneficial to search during the off-peak rental season, which is typically in the fall and winter months.\n\n6. **Use Online Platforms:** Websites like Craigslist, Zillow, Apartments.com, and Trulia can be valuable resources to filter searches based on price, size, and location preferences.\n\n7. **Local Housing Resources:** Utilize local resources such as the Seattle Housing Authority or non-profit housing organizations that can offer guidance on finding affordable apartments.\n\n8. **Negotiate Rent:** In some cases, you might be able to negotiate the rent, especially if an apartment has been on the market for an extended period. \n\n9. **Word of Mouth:** Let friends, family, and colleagues know you\u2019re searching for a place. They might know someone who\u2019s renting out a large space for a good price.\n\nAlways remember to stay safe while apartment hunting by visiting apartments with a friend when possible and carefully reviewing any lease agreements before signing.",
